<collectingCountry box="[320,413,158,184]" name="Ecuador" pageId="36" pageNumber="247">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
and perhaps 
<collectingCountry box="[561,612,159,185]" name="Peru" pageId="36" pageNumber="247">Peru</collectingCountry>
(see below).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="36.[136,1452,158,581]" pageId="36" pageNumber="247">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,294,194,220]" pageId="36" pageNumber="247">Notes:—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Luer" authorityYear="1976" box="[294,547,194,220]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Pleurothallis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="36" pageNumber="247" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pennellia">
<emphasis box="[294,547,194,220]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="247">Pleurothallis pennellia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described from 
<collectingCountry box="[771,864,194,220]" name="Ecuador" pageId="36" pageNumber="247">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
on the basis of a specimen that flowered in cultivation at the Marie Selby Botanical Gardens (
<bibRefCitation author="Luer, C. A." box="[581,719,230,257]" pageId="36" pageNumber="247" pagination="38 - 201" refId="ref29250" refString="Luer, C. A. (1976 b) Miscellaneous species of Pleurothallis. Selbyana 3: 38 - 201." type="journal article" year="1976">Luer 1976b</bibRefCitation>
). Luer compared it with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Luer" authorityYear="1982" baseAuthorityName="Ames" baseAuthorityYear="1923" box="[1002,1144,230,256]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="36" pageNumber="247" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="scandens">
<emphasis box="[1002,1144,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="247">M. scandens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but described it as having a much less prolific plant. The plant that served as 
<typeStatus box="[712,760,267,293]" pageId="36" pageNumber="247">type</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Luer" authorityYear="1976" box="[799,932,266,292]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Pleurothallis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="36" pageNumber="247" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pennellia">
<emphasis box="[799,932,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="247">P. pennellia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
eventually became prolific in cultivation, just like specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Luer" authorityYear="1982" baseAuthorityName="Ames" baseAuthorityYear="1923" box="[344,486,302,328]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="36" pageNumber="247" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="scandens">
<emphasis box="[344,486,302,328]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="247">M. scandens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, prompting 
<bibRefCitation author="Luer, C. A." box="[627,763,302,329]" pageId="36" pageNumber="247" pagination="1 - 128" refId="ref29681" refString="Luer, C. A. (1992) Icones pleurothallidinarum IX. Systematic of Myoxanthus. Addenda to Platystele, Pleurothallis, subgenus Scopula and Scaphosepalum (Orchidaceae). Monographs in Systematic Botany, Missouri Botanical Garden 44: 1 - 128." type="journal article" year="1992">Luer (1992)</bibRefCitation>
to place it under the synonymy of that species (
<bibRefCitation author="Luer, C. A." box="[1315,1439,302,328]" pageId="36" pageNumber="247" pagination="1 - 128" refId="ref29681" refString="Luer, C. A. (1992) Icones pleurothallidinarum IX. Systematic of Myoxanthus. Addenda to Platystele, Pleurothallis, subgenus Scopula and Scaphosepalum (Orchidaceae). Monographs in Systematic Botany, Missouri Botanical Garden 44: 1 - 128." type="journal article" year="1992">Luer 1992</bibRefCitation>
). However, based on the original description and illustration of the 
<typeStatus box="[884,935,339,365]" pageId="36" pageNumber="247">type</typeStatus>
, even with the prolific habit, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rojas-Alv. &amp; Karremans" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Rojas-Alv. &amp; Karremans" baseAuthorityYear="2021" box="[1271,1424,338,364]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="36" pageNumber="247" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pennellius">
<emphasis box="[1271,1424,338,364]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="247">M. pennellius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is still easily distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Luer" authorityYear="1982" baseAuthorityName="Ames" baseAuthorityYear="1923" box="[472,612,374,400]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="36" pageNumber="247" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="scandens">
<emphasis box="[472,612,374,400]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="247">M. scandens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Luer" authorityYear="1982" baseAuthorityName="Ames" baseAuthorityYear="1923" box="[787,927,374,400]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="36" pageNumber="247" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="scandens">
<emphasis box="[787,927,374,400]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="247">M. scandens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in its sepals with an obtuse to rounded apex 
<emphasis box="[1421,1444,375,400]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="247">vs</emphasis>
. acute, narrowly ovate petals slightly contracted above the middle, 
<emphasis box="[872,902,411,436]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="247">vs.</emphasis>
wider basally then conspicuously contracted into a thickened apex and a lip with two longitudinal lamellae above the middle 
<emphasis box="[973,996,447,472]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="247">vs</emphasis>
. with two longitudinal lamellae from the base to near the apex, a short clinandrium 
<emphasis box="[608,638,483,508]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="247">vs.</emphasis>
long-hooded. None of the specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Luer" authorityYear="1982" baseAuthorityName="Ames" baseAuthorityYear="1923" box="[1092,1232,482,508]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="36" pageNumber="247" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="scandens">
<emphasis box="[1092,1232,482,508]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="247">M. scandens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
studied here shares any of these features. We agree with 
<bibRefCitation author="Pupulin, F. &amp; Bogarin, D. &amp; Fernandez, M." box="[555,790,518,544]" pageId="36" pageNumber="247" pagination="467 - 473" refId="ref31029" refString="Pupulin, F., Bogarin, D. &amp; Fernandez, M. (2010) On the identity of Myoxanthus scandens (Orchidaceae: Pleurothallidinae), with a new species from Costa Rica. Lankesteriana 9: 467 - 473." type="journal article" year="2010">
Pupulin 
<emphasis box="[650,707,518,544]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="247">et al.</emphasis>
(2010)
</bibRefCitation>
that the photo of a Peruvian plant labelled 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Luer" authorityYear="1982" baseAuthorityName="Ames" baseAuthorityYear="1923" box="[1281,1422,518,544]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="36" pageNumber="247" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="scandens">
<emphasis box="[1281,1422,518,544]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="247">M. scandens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation author="Zelenko, H. &amp; Bermudez, P." box="[136,460,554,580]" pageId="36" pageNumber="247" refId="ref32552" refString="Zelenko, H. &amp; Bermudez, P. (2008) Orchids: species of Peru. ZAI, Quito, 407 pp." type="book" year="2008">Zelenko &amp; Bermúdez (2008)</bibRefCitation>
fits the description of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rojas-Alv. &amp; Karremans" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Rojas-Alv. &amp; Karremans" baseAuthorityYear="2021" box="[713,865,554,580]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="36" pageNumber="247" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pennellius">
<emphasis box="[713,865,554,580]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="247">M. pennellius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
